	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The C64 is a completely insane platform and the whole C64 developpement scene is completely insane. It's really surprising how the system is only able to do crap natively, but how it can be tweaked to do absolutely awesome thing by fooling the VIC II (C64's ppu) with tricky timing and stuff.
<br />Also, the CPU and VIC II acess to video RAM alternatively each cycle, so it is possible to write and read VRAM at any time, at the price of very low CPU frequency (it's twice slower than NES' : less than 1 MHz !!)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


