	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I said something LIKE. I didn't command you to go out and make something better.
<br />
<br />But yeah you could probably do something closer to that if you were using PAL (the vast majority of C64 demos are in PAL because most sceners (people who make demos) are in Europe) and chopped off some scanlines. Even if you didn't remove a whole bunch of scanlines you could probably do some cool 3D effects. I mean PAL gives you 70 lines of VBlank to work with, so that's 3.5x the amount of VBlank time to work with compared to NTSC. So if the only bottleneck in your program is VBlank, you could draw 3.5x more dots per frame or speed up your updates without extending VBlank.
<br />
<br />And you don't need a whole lot of dots to make a decent looking 3D object. Look at this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eQ-OcS2Gwvk" class="postlink">NES demo</a> for instance <a href="http://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=31539" class="postlink">(ROM here)</a>.
<br />
<br />But what you've got right now is great. If you want to do something else with it, that's your choice.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
