		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">CartCollector wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But what you've got right now is great. If you want to do something else with it, that's your choice.</div>
<br />
<br />I can only work on such fun stuff in short bursts, e.g. like during those two vacation weeks I just had. Now it'll rest again for a while, until another window opens where I can dedicate some time to it. That's why I try to work very focused towards my goal.
<br />
<br />What I can offer is my code though. The dots positions and directions are stored in the "XPOS", "YPOS" and "CURRDIR" arrays and they're accessed through xposPtr, yposPtr and currdirPtr. 
<br />
<br />If you want to experiment with it, you can just apply another movment code by tweaking lines 252-327. A and X are free to use there, Y indexes the current dot <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

